Author: stuki
Content: Heck no. The runtime is state of the art. So are many/most of the important libraries. Until another environment available ex Windows get close to that, java is solid. Generally speaking, languages with 'nice' features are a dime a dozen. It's the runtimes and ecosystems that are hard to duplicate.\n
